  "texts": [
    "In the unsupervised setting, the constitutive model is incorporated in a finite element solver, yielding a displacement field for a specific boundary value problem.",
    "The computed field, together with measurement data, yields a residual that is referred to as the modified constitutive relation error (mCRE) [407][408][409], which is minimized to improve the constitutive relation [410,411].",
    "Instead of formulating the mismatch in terms of displacements, [412,413] formulate it in terms of boundary forces.",
    "For an in-depth overview of constitutive model substitution in deep learning, see [32].",
    "Identification of model parametersIdentification of model parameters is achieved by assuming an underlying model and training a NN to predict its parameters for a given input."
